.TH "host1x_device_init" 9 "host1x_device_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
host1x_device_init \- initialize a host1x logical device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" host1x_device_init
.BI "(struct host1x_device *device "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
host1x logical device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The driver for the host1x logical device can call this during execution of
its \fIhost1x_driver.probe\fP implementation to initialize each of its clients.
The client drivers access the subsystem specific driver data using the
\fIhost1x_client.parent\fP field and driver data associated with it (usually by
calling \fBdev_get_drvdata\fP).
